      "writtenOn": "2020-05-21T20:18:54Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I could add an SK_PMColor4fBLACK, I\u0027d rather not add the overload since most use of separate R,G,B,A fields would be in our own tests and an initializer list isn\u0027t that hard to read. It\u0027s definitely important that we preserve the expectation that the color is premul.\n\nRegarding Brian\u0027s comments, I like that currently the type is consistent with the color type of GrPaint. I think this would mean that if we have other alpha types for a GrRTC, we\u0027d correct the values to maintain expectations. Do all GrRTCs have kPremul currently?",
      "parentUuid": "4f03f374_f03e4382",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 245,
        "startChar": 10,
        "endLine": 245,
        "endChar": 14
      },
      "revId": "0a1e06eb41b140f56c237f766345429e3c5f3169",
